original_title: Brooklyn: New Lots Avenue - Church Avenue
text:
(1)
New Lots Road, south side, west of Church Ave., showing the Derrick Remsen house erected by him in 1725; later owned by William Williamson; William F. Ryerson owned it in 1922. It was razed in 1927. If standing in 1936, it would be in Rockaway Parkway in front of No. 488.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, another view.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3)
The same.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
